<subSubSection id="26DF6534FFEE5C2AFF6C9F4BDDABFCDF" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" type="key">
<key id="1A54618EFFEE5C2AFF6C9F4BDDABFCDF" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">
<keyStep id="D5312E1AFFEE5C2AFF6C9F4BDDACFF3D" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="77" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">
<paragraph id="6E7A36BFFFEE5C2DFF6C9F4BDD6FF906" blockId="3.[195,1104,1644,1732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">
<keyLead id="D534958AFFEE5C2DFF6C9F4BDD6FF906" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">
1. Pro- and meso-outer claws each with an obtuse tooth at base in male; aedeagus: conjoint dorsal plate of parameres with acute lateral angels, ventral process of each paramere strongly curved at base..... 
<taxonomicName id="A9C54D3CFFEE5C2DFCE29F8ADACBF906" authority="Yang &amp; Yang, 2013" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2013" box="[845,1012,1709,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parameratus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5CB1EAADFFEE5C2DFCE29F8ADACBF906" box="[845,1012,1709,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="76">L. parameratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="478257D6FFEE5C2DFC539F8ADD6FF906" box="[1020,1104,1709,1732]" pageId="3" pageNumber="76" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E7A36BFFFE95C2AFEA1998FDDACFF3D" blockId="4.[270,1171,167,255]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<keyLead id="D534958AFFE95C2AFEA1998FDDACFF3D" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">– Pro- and meso-outer claws simple in male; aedeagus: conjoint dorsal plate of parameres with rounded lateral angels, ventral process of each paramere normal at base.......................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="D5312E1AFFE95C2AFEA89830DDACFE5C" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<paragraph id="6E7A36BFFFE95C2AFEA89830DDABFEAD" blockId="4.[263,1172,279,367]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<keyLead id="D534958AFFE95C2AFEA89830DDABFEAD" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
2. Antennae wider in female than in male; aedeagus: conjoint dorsal plate of parameres narrowly emarginated in middle of apical margin, with lateral margins of emargination bent ventrally................ 
<taxonomicName id="A9C54D3CFFE95C2AFC06987FDD06FEAD" authority="Yang &amp; Yang, 2013" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2013" box="[937,1081,344,367]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrigenus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5CB1EAADFFE95C2AFC06987FDD06FEAD" box="[937,1081,344,367]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">L. nigrigenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="478257D6FFE95C2AFBEF987FDDABFEAD" box="[1088,1172,344,367]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E7A36BFFFE95C2AFEA198A0DDACFE5C" blockId="4.[270,1171,390,414]" box="[270,1171,390,414]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<keyLead id="D534958AFFE95C2AFEA198A0DDACFE5C" box="[270,1171,390,414]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">– Antennae narrower in female than in male; aedeagus not like above........ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="D5312E1AFFE95C2AFEA89891DDACFDDC" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<paragraph id="6E7A36BFFFE95C2AFEA89891DDABFE2C" blockId="4.[263,1172,438,494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<keyLead id="D534958AFFE95C2AFEA89891DDABFE2C" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
3. Head, pronotum and elytra yellowish brown, elytra darkened at apices........................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="A9C54D3CFFE95C2AFC0D98F0DD06FE2C" authority="Yang &amp; Yang, 2013" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2013" box="[930,1081,471,494]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroapicis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5CB1EAADFFE95C2AFC0D98F0DD06FE2C" box="[930,1081,471,494]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">L. nigroapicis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="478257D6FFE95C2AFBEF98F0DDABFE2C" box="[1088,1172,471,494]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E7A36BFFFE95C2AFEA19B20DDACFDDC" blockId="4.[270,1171,518,542]" box="[270,1171,518,542]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<keyLead id="D534958AFFE95C2AFEA19B20DDACFDDC" box="[270,1171,518,542]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">– Head, pronotum and elytra black, at most yellow at clypeus............... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="D5312E1AFFE95C2AFEA89B11DDABFCDF" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<paragraph id="6E7A36BFFFE95C2AFEA89B11DDABFD6F" blockId="4.[263,1172,566,686]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<keyLead id="D534958AFFE95C2AFEA89B11DDABFD6F" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
4. Aedeagus: conjoint dorsal plate of parameres each side with two teeth near lateral angle on inner surface, ventral process of each paramere distinctly shorter than conjoint dorsal plate, laterophyses normal at apices................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="A9C54D3CFFE95C2AFC939BB0DDABFD6F" authority="(Wittmer, 1995)" baseAuthorityName="Wittmer" baseAuthorityYear="1995" box="[828,1172,661,686]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kuatunensis">
<emphasis id="5CB1EAADFFE95C2AFC939BB0DAE3FD6C" box="[828,988,662,686]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">L. kuatunensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="0A544B4EFFE95C2AFC459BB2DDB4FD6F" author="Wittmer W" box="[1002,1163,661,685]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77" pagination="171 - 286" refId="ref5232" refString="Wittmer W. 1995. Zur Kenntnis Gattung Athemus Lewis (Col. Cantharidae). Entomol Basil. 18: 171 - 286." type="journal article" year="1995">Wittmer, 1995</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6E7A36BFFFE95C2AFEA19BE1DDABFCDF" blockId="4.[270,1172,709,797]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
<keyLead id="D534958AFFE95C2AFEA19BE1DDABFCDF" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">
– Aedeagus: conjoint dorsal plate of parameres without any tooth on inner surface, ventral process of each paramere nearly as long as conjoint dorsal plate, laterophyses bifurcated at apices....................... 
<taxonomicName id="A9C54D3CFFE95C2AFC039A21DD06FCDF" authority="Yang &amp; Yang, 2013" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="2013" box="[940,1081,773,797]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifurcatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5CB1EAADFFE95C2AFC039A21DD06FCDF" box="[940,1081,773,797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="77">L. bifurcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="478257D6FFE95C2AFBEF9A21DDABFCDF" box="[1088,1172,774,797]" pageId="4" pageNumber="77" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
</subSubSection>
